commentary: Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Powell, OUT taken by the keeper nice loop to the ball, changes his linen to outside off. Rovman is dragged forward to defend, but he's playing for turn that isn't there. At best the ball turned only gently, and takes his outside edge. Mushfiqur holds on, standing up to the stumps. Wait a minute, Rovman has reviewed this. Substitute Carlos Brathwaite has come on and is arguing with the umpires. The commentators on air saying it could be something to do with number of fielders inside the circle/outside it. Brathwaite is still in the middle and gesturing, standing alongside Hope and Powell. On the other side of the pitch the Bangladesh players are gathered. It ends in Brathwaite walking off, and Powell is walking back too. So he's definitely out.

commentary: Paul to Soumya Sarkar, no run loud appeal, not given They've gone for a review. Angled into the batsman again, strikes him flush on the pad in front of middle - but was the angle taking it too far down? Soumya had gone too far across and was trying to work it to midwicket again, but played all around it. Fortunately for him, ball tracking shows it to be clipping and it's umpire's call, so the original decision stays and Soumya survives. Bad shot though.

Fortunately for him, ball tracking shows it to be clipping and it's umpire's call, so the original decision stays and Soumya survives. Bad shot though.

They appeal and go for the review when it's not given. Looked like it would miss leg, but West Indies have to review. Ultra edge shows no bat, but it's a lot closer than it looked. The ball was clipping leg stump, so it's umpire's call. West Indies retain their review, but Soumya survives

commentary: Powell to Tamim Iqbal, FOUR runs Bangladesh have won by eight wickets, with 11.3 overs to spare Fuller ball, wide of off, and he goes for the drive, opening the face once again and beating the man at short third man to get the winning runs. Comprehensive win, and Bangladesh take the series 2-1
